WEBVTT

00:03.138 --> 00:05.040
Welcome to the Life Church Podcast.

00:06.422 --> 00:11.588
We are an Acts 2 42 community, a family on a mission to bring a life of Jesus to warranty.

00:13.129 --> 00:22.460
We hope you're ready to hear what God has to say to you today through His Word and by His Spirit.

00:23.100 --> 00:31.570
We've been walking through Romans together, the Roman road, and it's my privilege to finish, well, lots of finish you off.

00:32.002 --> 00:34.646
Well, maybe it will feel finished off in half an hour, who knows?

00:35.086 --> 00:37.630
But it's my privilege to finish that series this evening.

00:38.291 --> 00:49.767
And it's been good and important to talk about these things because one of the things that's important to us as a church is that we are a gospel centric church.

00:50.248 --> 00:52.250
The gospel is at the heart of what we do.

00:53.011 --> 01:00.562
And often in church you can get distracted by all kinds of things, like how good is the youth ministry,

01:00.802 --> 01:03.326
Are we serving people, hospitality properly?

01:03.907 --> 01:05.790
Are people in a life group?

01:05.810 --> 01:06.951
What's the worship light?

01:07.011 --> 01:07.853
Is it too loud?

01:07.873 --> 01:08.854
Is it too quiet?

01:09.495 --> 01:16.686
All of these different things, but they can become a distraction if you don't keep the main thing, the main thing.

01:16.726 --> 01:22.735
And the main thing is this, that Christ Jesus came into the world to say sinners.

01:23.256 --> 01:24.418
That's the main thing.

01:24.778 --> 01:26.341
That's the message of the gospel.

01:26.541 --> 01:26.901
All right.

01:27.342 --> 01:29.906
So from time to, it's good to talk about the other stuff.

01:30.210 --> 01:32.574
Because all those other things I mentioned, they're really important.

01:32.994 --> 01:43.630
But the most important thing is how we've come to be here and what God has done in our lives and what a difference that's made and the basis on which we believe what we believe.

01:44.672 --> 01:48.177
So at the Apostle Paul, he planted a church in a place called Corinth.

01:48.858 --> 01:55.448
He was there for a year and a half and he wrote to them a few years later and he said to them a few things.

01:55.488 --> 01:59.154
He said, I want to remind you of the gospel.

01:59.586 --> 02:10.697
He says it's of first importance that Christ died for our sins according to the scriptures that he was buried and that he was raised again three days later according to the scriptures.

02:11.197 --> 02:15.561
Paul said those things because the gospel was the most important thing.

02:16.342 --> 02:25.811
And as we've gone through this book of Romans together, we've gone down this Roman road, which takes us on this journey through the scriptures, the book of Romans in salvation.

02:26.151 --> 02:29.074
And that's where we will go again this evening.

02:29.570 --> 02:33.174
But the gospel is by this gospel that we save.

02:33.234 --> 02:34.215
That's what Paul says.

02:34.956 --> 02:41.103
Tim Keller, he's passed away now, but he was a pastor and a writer.

02:41.924 --> 02:49.092
I always find what he says, easy to digest because he puts things in really simple but profound terms.

02:49.452 --> 02:52.135
And this is what Tim Keller said that the gospel is.

02:52.175 --> 02:58.162
He said, the gospel is this, that we are more sinful and flawed in ourselves

02:58.274 --> 03:00.056
than we ever dared believe.

03:01.298 --> 03:10.008
Yet at the same time, we are more loved and accepted in Jesus Christ than we ever dared to hope.

03:10.789 --> 03:23.905
And that is the message of the gospel tonight, that we are sinful and flawed, and we need a Savior, and His name is Jesus, and He has loved and accepted us more than we would ever dare to hope.

03:24.786 --> 03:27.730
And so, these last few weeks we've been on this Roman road,

03:28.194 --> 03:31.758
First week, we were reminded by Dell.

03:31.878 --> 03:33.680
I think it was cast in my mind back.

03:34.280 --> 03:36.282
We were reminded from Romans 3.23.

03:36.362 --> 03:40.847
The first step on this Roman road is the all of sinned.

03:41.488 --> 03:52.659
The Bible says in Romans 3.23, it says, there's no difference between Jews and Gentiles for all of sinned and full short of the glory of God.

03:53.059 --> 03:55.602
That was our need.

03:55.810 --> 03:59.515
That's where we find ourselves before we find Christ.

03:59.575 --> 04:01.478
We are sinners and we are lost.

04:02.159 --> 04:06.545
And then in the second week, we talked about the fact that Christ died for us.

04:07.306 --> 04:08.668
The consequence of sin.

04:08.728 --> 04:17.119
The Bible says, for the wages of sin is death, but the gift of God is eternal life through Jesus Christ, our Lord.

04:17.379 --> 04:23.328
The Bible reminds us in Romans chapter five, for while we were yet sinners, Christ died for us.

04:23.688 --> 04:25.170
This is the good news.

04:25.410 --> 04:29.236
that Christ died for us so that we don't need to stay in our sin.

04:29.917 --> 04:40.333
And then last week, Jason brilliantly preached to us from the Scriptures, Romans chapter 10, verse nine, that we're invited to confess Jesus as Lord.

04:40.413 --> 04:49.147
The Bible says that if we declare with our mouths, Jesus is Lord and we believe in our heart that God raised him from the dead, we will be saved.

04:50.129 --> 04:52.432
Jesus has authority over my life.

04:52.472 --> 04:53.554
That's what we say.

04:53.762 --> 05:03.311
when we say Jesus is Lord, Jesus is my Lord, not sin, not comfort, not my agenda, not my selfishness, but Jesus is my Lord.

05:03.591 --> 05:10.097
And that's what happens at the moment of salvation when we say yes to Christ and we become a new creation.

05:12.199 --> 05:23.730
This evening, what I wanna close this series out with is I was having an understanding from the Bible of the security and certainty that we can have

05:23.874 --> 05:29.702
now that we are Christians, now that we have accepted God's free gift of salvation.

05:30.964 --> 05:39.155
It's a verse in Philippians chapter one, which says this, Paul says this to the church, he says, being confident of this.

05:39.515 --> 05:43.240
And this is what I speak over you this evening as followers of Christ.

05:43.260 --> 05:47.987
You're on this road, this journey of following Jesus, this road of salvation.

05:48.047 --> 05:53.554
And this is what I pray over you and myself this evening that being confident of this

05:54.082 --> 06:03.154
that he who began a good work in you will carry it on to completion until the day of Jesus Christ.

06:03.795 --> 06:14.970
I believe God's heart for you is that now that you're on this journey of following him, that you're following well, you're following faithfully, and you'll know what it is to have that assurance of faith.

06:15.030 --> 06:21.298
You understand what Christ has done for you, not just in that moment of salvation, but every day

06:21.410 --> 06:24.353
as you follow Christ as his Lord of your life.

06:25.274 --> 06:33.243
I want us to understand the security and certainty of our salvation, it rests on the work of Christ.

06:33.723 --> 06:35.365
That's what it rests on.

06:35.705 --> 06:45.816
It's because of what Christ has done for you and me this evening that we can be confident and certain of this gift of salvation that God has given to us.

06:46.297 --> 06:51.282
It's not by our works, it's because of his work

06:51.458 --> 06:52.279
in us.

06:52.879 --> 06:54.801
It's not about us doing enough.

06:55.582 --> 07:00.447
It's not about us thinking today, am I good enough to be saved?

07:01.107 --> 07:03.750
Did I pray hard enough?

07:04.391 --> 07:06.553
Did I sin too much?

07:07.454 --> 07:09.816
Okay, that's not the nature of salvation.

07:09.836 --> 07:17.564
When we start to think and act like that, what we're doing actually is we're actually flicking back to works.

07:18.084 --> 07:19.986
We're actually saying like, if I'm good enough,

07:20.322 --> 07:22.084
then I'll stay saved.

07:22.104 --> 07:24.888
If I pray enough, I'll stay saved.

07:24.908 --> 07:28.373
If I don't sin today, I'll stay saved.

07:28.393 --> 07:39.327
What we do when we say that is we move away from the finished work of Jesus on the cross, which we understand is by grace.

07:39.627 --> 07:40.689
It's not by work.

07:40.709 --> 07:41.810
So that's what the Bible says.

07:42.251 --> 07:47.858
And all of a sudden, particularly when we've been a Christian for a while, we think, oh, we're doing really well.

07:48.034 --> 07:50.496
like we're really spiritual, we're really holy.

07:50.737 --> 07:55.601
So actually, it's not just about what Jesus did on the cross 2000 years ago.

07:55.641 --> 08:12.357
It's not only by grace, I've been saved, but actually it's a bit to do in my works, because if I'm just good enough, if I just pray enough, if I'm just kind enough to others, that will earn me enough brownie points in order that I can be saved.

08:12.377 --> 08:13.418
No, that's not true.

08:14.119 --> 08:17.842
And when we think like that, what we do is actually,

08:17.954 --> 08:19.896
we do discredit to the cross.

08:20.437 --> 08:28.307
Because if it was possible for you and me to be saved through our own works, then there was no need for Jesus to come.

08:28.707 --> 08:36.897
But there was need for Jesus to come because all of sin and fallen short of the glory of God, the wages of sin are death.

08:37.538 --> 08:44.206
And we understand in our lives what it is to be free from that because of the work that Christ did on the cross.

08:44.626 --> 08:47.730
But what we need to do is we need to understand

08:47.970 --> 08:56.139
that the work of Christ on the cross continues to be enough right throughout our life until we get to heaven.

08:57.000 --> 09:00.964
And that's what Paul wants to remind us of this evening from the Scriptures.

09:02.686 --> 09:12.216
In Romans 10, verse 13, he says these words, everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved.

09:12.877 --> 09:17.362
Like it's a statement of fact, it's absolutely true.

09:17.826 --> 09:22.791
There was no doubt in Paul's mind when he wrote those words.

09:23.612 --> 09:31.841
When we respond in faith to Christ, our standing before God rests on his faithfulness and not ours.

09:31.861 --> 09:38.728
So there's three brief things, just about that verse, and then just a couple of things before I finish.

09:38.748 --> 09:40.570
So three things about that verse.

09:40.590 --> 09:43.433
First of all, is that word, everyone.

09:44.053 --> 09:44.754
Everyone.

09:44.994 --> 09:48.238
The verse is, everyone who calls on the name of the law will be saved.

09:48.959 --> 09:57.990
That reminds us of the inclusivity of the gospel and the certainty that everyone can be saved.

09:58.270 --> 09:58.550
Okay?

09:59.031 --> 10:02.675
This evening, it doesn't matter what you've been like.

10:02.755 --> 10:04.277
It doesn't matter what you've done.

10:04.297 --> 10:09.423
The fact is that the invitation from the verse is for everyone.

10:09.984 --> 10:11.666
It's available to everyone.

10:11.874 --> 10:17.240
This breaks down every barrier of ethnicity, particularly in the context that it was written.

10:17.280 --> 10:19.703
It was written to Jews and Gentiles.

10:20.284 --> 10:26.211
And Paul was reminding them that everyone who calls on the name of the law can be saved.

10:26.231 --> 10:33.319
That everyone demolishes every boundary that humans would try and put around God's grace.

10:33.399 --> 10:39.186
You know, we can think, well, the gospel isn't for everyone because surely it's not for that person.

10:39.266 --> 10:42.491
or it's not for that person, or maybe even it's not for me.

10:43.192 --> 10:47.058
But this evening, God doesn't want us to limit His grace.

10:47.619 --> 10:51.965
God's grace does not need protecting by you and me.

10:52.045 --> 10:54.609
God's grace goes to everyone.

10:54.649 --> 11:01.981
And we can be confident this evening and have that assurance of faith because we are part of the everyone, you and me.

11:02.301 --> 11:04.725
God's grace has reached into our lives.

11:05.125 --> 11:08.210
We don't need to be the grace police.

11:09.090 --> 11:13.274
And notice that the text also says everyone and not everybody.

11:13.875 --> 11:17.719
There's this personal confession of faith that we need to make.

11:18.099 --> 11:22.984
Let me ask you this evening, are you part of the everyone tonight?

11:23.364 --> 11:30.532
Was there a moment in your life where you confess that Jesus was Lord and you believed in your heart that God raised him from the dead?

11:30.852 --> 11:34.175
The Bible says that when we do that, we become a child of God.

11:34.876 --> 11:36.978
So if you want that assurance tonight,

11:37.250 --> 11:41.455
then you must ensure that you are part of the everyone.

11:41.896 --> 11:44.399
So there's the inclusivity of the gospel in that.

11:44.659 --> 11:54.552
The second thing that we see in this verse, everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved is that we see the simplicity of the gospel.

11:55.573 --> 11:59.758
It is gloriously simple, okay?

11:59.778 --> 12:01.841
That doesn't mean it's ineffective.

12:02.902 --> 12:04.764
It doesn't mean it's second class.

12:05.105 --> 12:06.226
It just means

12:06.434 --> 12:09.758
that the gospel is gloriously simple.

12:10.259 --> 12:19.050
And what happens is often we can try and make it more than it is in terms of how people access the gospel.

12:19.671 --> 12:21.573
It's all about the position of your heart.

12:22.314 --> 12:27.460
The simplicity of the gospel is where is your heart in relation to God?

12:27.601 --> 12:30.084
Have you called on the name of the Lord?

12:30.584 --> 12:35.090
This means if you genuinely appeal to God through Jesus Christ,

12:35.234 --> 12:36.015
for salvation.

12:36.135 --> 12:42.444
Have you this evening acknowledged your need of him and asked him to save you.

12:42.464 --> 12:50.655
We simply need to confess Jesus is Lord and believe in our heart that God raised him from the dead.

12:51.155 --> 12:54.760
It's about believing and it's not about doing.

12:55.040 --> 12:56.562
We need to remember that.

12:56.582 --> 12:58.765
It's about the position of our heart.

12:59.206 --> 13:05.234
And what we need to do in order to respond to this verse and to have that assurance of faith

13:05.346 --> 13:12.336
that we belong to Christ is, we simply call on the name of the Lord and he promises to rescue us.

13:12.737 --> 13:19.307
I love the narrative in Luke 23 where there are three men on crosses.

13:19.988 --> 13:24.515
Jesus is in the middle and there are two thieves on either side of him.

13:25.536 --> 13:34.770
One of the thieves turns to Jesus and he says, if the Bible says that he cursed Jesus, he said, Jesus, if you're the son of God, then you can get us down off here

13:35.010 --> 13:36.071
Like, do your thing.

13:36.111 --> 13:39.595
He wasn't really interested in who Jesus was.

13:40.016 --> 13:43.019
He was just interested in getting out of that situation he was in.

13:44.140 --> 13:49.586
But a glorious picture of the gospel of what Christ does for us was the other thief on the cross.

13:50.667 --> 13:58.135
The other thief on the cross, he recognized that Jesus did not deserve to be in that space in that place.

13:59.237 --> 14:04.082
And he turns to Jesus and he says these words, and this was his confession of faith.

14:04.962 --> 14:10.490
He said, Jesus, remember me when you come into your kingdom.

14:10.510 --> 14:12.954
And Jesus' response is instantaneous.

14:13.374 --> 14:16.539
Jesus tells him to do nothing.

14:17.060 --> 14:21.546
Jesus didn't have the thief on the cross, didn't have any time for good works.

14:22.107 --> 14:26.073
There wasn't any time for an alpha course or baptism classes.

14:26.714 --> 14:31.761
There wasn't any room to work through the values of life church, Acts 2, 42.

14:33.023 --> 14:34.866
He couldn't make any amends.

14:34.946 --> 14:39.913
All he could do in that moment was holy trust in Jesus' name.

14:40.674 --> 14:42.577
And Jesus says these words to him.

14:43.358 --> 14:49.326
He says to him, truly, I tell you, today you will be with me in paradise.

14:49.727 --> 14:55.835
You see, there was no space for works, there was no space to make amends.

14:56.276 --> 15:00.562
In that moment, all the thief on the cross could simply do

15:00.706 --> 15:02.809
was trust Christ as his Savior.

15:03.090 --> 15:08.758
He had to rely wholly on the finished work of Christ on the cross.

15:09.560 --> 15:10.601
And that's what he did.

15:10.641 --> 15:18.293
That moment of personal interaction and confession, he recognized that Jesus was the answer.

15:18.834 --> 15:29.330
So we have to remember when we listen, when we hear that verse, everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved.

15:29.538 --> 15:35.948
We have to remember live church this evening that it's not about me, but it's about he.

15:36.449 --> 15:38.172
It's about what he has done.

15:38.212 --> 15:43.741
It's about not about what I might do, but it's about what he has done.

15:44.082 --> 15:50.492
And that's where our assurance of faith comes from, because we recognize that it's nothing to do with us.

15:51.033 --> 15:54.258
All we have to do is we have to confess

15:54.370 --> 15:57.815
that Jesus is Lord and we have to put our faith and our trust in Him.

15:58.176 --> 16:04.024
Simply in the act of faith, we know what it is to pass over from death unto life.

16:04.385 --> 16:11.576
One Peter 2, 24 says, he himself bore our sins in his body on the tree.

16:12.036 --> 16:18.005
John 1 29, he is the Lamb of God who takes away the sins of the world.

16:18.486 --> 16:23.794
One Corinthians 1 verse 30, he is our righteousness

16:23.906 --> 16:25.808
holiness and redemption.

16:26.549 --> 16:27.610
You get the theme.

16:27.650 --> 16:29.251
It's about him.

16:29.291 --> 16:31.874
It's about what he has done.

16:32.314 --> 16:33.876
It's not about what we do.

16:34.777 --> 16:37.359
And then the final thing is this that we see in this text.

16:38.800 --> 16:41.023
Those words will be saved.

16:42.444 --> 16:45.727
This reminds us this evening of the certainty of the gospel.

16:46.188 --> 16:47.529
It's absolutely certain.

16:50.151 --> 16:52.754
This is the promise that God gives to us

16:53.058 --> 17:00.085
He keeps his promise, our salvation rests on God's grip on us, not our grip on him.

17:00.525 --> 17:03.028
Listen to what Jesus says in John chapter 10.

17:03.828 --> 17:08.513
He says, my sheep listen to my voice and I know them and they follow me.

17:09.314 --> 17:12.197
I give them eternal life and they shall never perish.

17:12.957 --> 17:15.880
No one will snatch them out of my hand.

17:16.601 --> 17:21.906
Romans eight verse one, there is now no condemnation for those

17:22.050 --> 17:23.612
who are in Christ Jesus.

17:24.393 --> 17:32.304
The amplified version said there's no guilty verdict, there's no punishment for those who are in Christ Jesus.

17:33.045 --> 17:42.278
And there's the ongoing certainty of the gospel that we can enjoy, that we can have that assurance of faith in.

17:42.338 --> 17:51.250
We need to understand this evening live church that you are not on a probationary salvation.

17:51.842 --> 18:01.214
Okay, God isn't looking at your life and saying, well, depending on how well they do in the next six months, we'll see if they get through.

18:01.935 --> 18:20.338
Because as soon as you start to talk or think like that, what you're doing is you're ignoring the work of the cross and you're actually saying, well, Lord, I understand that the cross is enough to save me, but I don't believe that the cross is enough to keep me.

18:20.578 --> 18:27.047
Let me tell you tonight, live church, the cross is enough to save you and the cross is enough to keep you.

18:27.367 --> 18:30.972
The finished work of the cross is enough.

18:30.992 --> 18:49.517
As soon as we start to think it's about us, how good we are, how well we do, how little we sin, how much we pray, all of a sudden, what we're doing is we switching to a gospel of works where it's about how good I do.

18:49.957 --> 18:50.578
Listen.

18:50.786 --> 18:55.492
Our salvation has never been based upon how well we do.

18:55.512 --> 19:00.078
It's based on his mercy and it's based on his kindness.

19:00.479 --> 19:03.042
Listen to Titus chapter three verse five.

19:03.984 --> 19:13.336
He saved us not because of works done by us in righteousness, but according to his own mercy.

19:14.518 --> 19:20.626
Not only were we saved according to his mercy, but we continue to be saved

19:20.802 --> 19:24.446
because of His mercy and His grace.

19:25.187 --> 19:29.132
We need to understand that it's Him who keeps us.

19:29.953 --> 19:42.288
If we think it's about us and what we do, then what we're seeking to do in that is we're seeking to add to the cross our good works in order that we are saved.

19:42.308 --> 19:50.738
But let me tell you, the equation is this, that Jesus plus nothing equals salvation.

19:50.914 --> 19:55.902
Jesus plus nothing equals salvation.

19:56.282 --> 20:06.458
We simply need to confess with our mouth Jesus is Lord and believe in our heart that God raised him from the dead and then we are saved.

20:07.259 --> 20:08.922
Here are some scriptures this evening.

20:09.423 --> 20:16.474
Reasons why you can be certain that you, that your salvation is sure.

20:17.716 --> 20:19.218
Romans 8 verse 30.

20:20.514 --> 20:32.025
Those he predestined, he also called, those he called, he also justified, those he justified, he also glorified.

20:32.585 --> 20:50.002
To be justified by God means being legally declared righteous, forgiven of all sins and accepted by God, not based on personal merit, but through faith in Jesus Christ and his finished work.

20:50.466 --> 21:02.640
It is an instantaneous, inevocable act of grace where Christ's righteousness is imputed to the believer, treating them as if they had never sinned.

21:04.482 --> 21:06.444
That's what it means to be justified.

21:07.065 --> 21:10.348
So listen, this evening you can be certain because you've been justified.

21:10.769 --> 21:16.135
Second, you can be certain because the Bible says that Jesus intercedes for you.

21:17.056 --> 21:18.898
Verse 34 of Romans 8.

21:19.330 --> 21:28.964
Jesus Christ who died more than that was raised to life is at the right hand of God and is also interceding for us.

21:29.525 --> 21:32.610
Jesus prays for the believers this evening.

21:33.712 --> 21:40.081
Third reason you can be certain, you can be certain because the Bible says that nothing can separate you from the love of God.

21:40.602 --> 21:41.904
Listen to what the Bible says.

21:43.086 --> 21:48.754
Romans 8 verse 39, for I am convinced that neither death nor life

21:49.058 --> 22:02.975
Neither angels nor demons, neither the present nor the future, nor anything else in all creation will be able to separate us from the love of God that is in Christ Jesus our Lord.

22:03.876 --> 22:10.164
Okay, this is the problem that we have with this doctrine sometimes.

22:11.706 --> 22:18.194
The problem is that we mix up sanctification and salvation.

22:19.362 --> 22:19.843
Okay?

22:20.363 --> 22:22.045
Sanctification and salvation.

22:22.425 --> 22:23.927
Both are really important.

22:23.947 --> 22:25.449
They're both things that you understand.

22:25.469 --> 22:26.410
Okay?

22:26.830 --> 22:35.880
Your salvation is a gift from God that is available through the finished work of Christ.

22:36.380 --> 22:40.164
The reason you're saved, it's nothing to do with you.

22:40.285 --> 22:42.487
All you have to do is accept it by faith.

22:42.887 --> 22:43.568
Okay?

22:43.588 --> 22:49.074
Your salvation is through faith in Christ alone.

22:49.154 --> 22:53.859
That is a gift that's been given to you, it's not by works.

22:54.820 --> 22:55.981
So that's salvation.

22:56.041 --> 23:00.346
That's a gift, it's given, you can't earn it.

23:01.507 --> 23:03.750
But then there's this thing called sanctification.

23:06.072 --> 23:08.094
This doesn't add to our salvation.

23:09.055 --> 23:13.901
Sanctification is the process whereby we become more like Jesus.

23:14.441 --> 23:15.803
We become more holy.

23:16.223 --> 23:18.866
We please Him with our lives.

23:18.946 --> 23:22.190
we become more surrendered to Him.

23:23.291 --> 23:25.453
Sin is less in our lives.

23:25.574 --> 23:27.876
That's the process of sanctification.

23:28.237 --> 23:39.529
The Bible says that we're being sanctified by the power of the Holy Spirit in us, we seek to live lives that please God, hopefully more and more.

23:39.870 --> 23:44.595
Maybe sometimes we have bad days here, but more and more, we want our lives to please Him.

23:44.916 --> 23:47.058
That's the process of sanctification.

23:47.266 --> 23:55.094
And the Bible says that one day, when we get to heaven, we will see him and we will become like him.

23:55.514 --> 23:57.196
We'll be fully sanctified.

23:57.756 --> 24:01.500
What we do is we get these two tied up together.

24:02.581 --> 24:09.248
What we do is we think that our salvation and our sanctification are like locked in together.

24:09.588 --> 24:15.314
We think that actually, if I'm doing really well, then I'm definitely saved.

24:15.394 --> 24:19.861
If I'm not doing really well, like our sanctification pulls our salvation down.

24:20.141 --> 24:21.443
Like it's nonsense, yeah?

24:21.804 --> 24:23.546
Salvation is here.

24:23.747 --> 24:25.069
That's a work of the cross.

24:25.389 --> 24:26.150
It's been done.

24:26.531 --> 24:27.372
It's complete.

24:27.673 --> 24:28.614
It's a gift.

24:28.634 --> 24:30.157
You just have to receive it.

24:30.477 --> 24:32.660
But sanctification is important as well.

24:32.981 --> 24:34.163
It's really important.

24:34.704 --> 24:41.554
If you've been saved, evidence that Christ is at work in you will be

24:41.666 --> 24:45.612
that you have a desire to do the things that God wants you to do.

24:46.013 --> 24:54.146
But listen, your desire for wanting to do those things that God wants you to do, it doesn't make you more saved.

24:54.166 --> 24:56.150
It does please the heart of God.

24:56.771 --> 24:57.612
It is good.

24:58.173 --> 25:00.136
It is good to be more like Jesus.

25:00.477 --> 25:03.562
Jesus says, if you love me, you'll keep my commands.

25:03.922 --> 25:08.690
Peter writes in the scripture, be holy because I am holy, yeah?

25:08.802 --> 25:12.165
It's a good thing, but it doesn't add to your salvation.

25:12.846 --> 25:16.690
All of us will have to give an account of our life before God.

25:17.170 --> 25:26.939
The decisions that we make, how we use our resources, how we use the gifts that God has given to us, all of us we will have to give an account of those things.

25:27.560 --> 25:33.305
But our salvation is only through what Christ has done for us.

25:33.325 --> 25:38.130
So I would say, as I look at scripture,

25:38.242 --> 25:53.239
this evening, if you have confessed with your mouth that Jesus is Lord and you've believed in your heart that God raised him from the dead, like I believe that you're saved and you can have an assurance of faith and salvation in what Christ has done for you, yeah?

25:53.759 --> 25:54.861
It's a done deal.

25:55.421 --> 26:01.348
And if that is your story, then there will be this desire in you to wanna please him.

26:01.948 --> 26:06.994
Now listen, I got baptized when I was 14 years old.

26:08.962 --> 26:13.908
I'm now 54, so that's that, 40 years ago, okay.

26:15.810 --> 26:19.213
I said yes to Jesus when I was very young, I was about four.

26:19.654 --> 26:21.876
I got baptized when I was 40, yeah?

26:22.317 --> 26:27.282
So salvation happened at some point back there when I believed Jesus as my savior.

26:27.703 --> 26:37.714
Let me tell you, and I say this gently, and I say this with respect, yeah, but I have done most of my sinning in my life

26:37.890 --> 26:39.212
since I was 14.

26:40.273 --> 26:44.338
Without doubt, yeah, I was saved between the age of four and 10.

26:45.019 --> 26:49.884
And since I was 14, I've been saved, my salvation is sure.

26:50.585 --> 26:52.307
It's because of what Christ has done.

26:52.748 --> 27:00.918
But I have, if I'm honest with you, in the last 40 years, I definitely sinned more than I did before I was 14.

27:00.938 --> 27:03.241
I mean, you know, give me a break.

27:03.281 --> 27:07.666
It's just like four times as long, isn't it?

27:07.726 --> 27:07.826
Yeah?

27:08.290 --> 27:15.697
But the thing is, this is why I want you to see the difference between salvation and sanctification, yeah?

27:16.257 --> 27:20.441
Salvation is sure, and it's a work of what Christ has done.

27:20.481 --> 27:28.529
Sanctification is my responsibility in the power of the Spirit to live my life in a way that's honoring to God.

27:28.889 --> 27:38.258
I mean, I'd like to say that my sanctification, if I was looking at you, is like up and to the right, constantly, but it's not, you know,

27:38.434 --> 27:47.526
You know, it's up here sometimes, maybe I have a bad day and maybe I sin and I have to say sorry to God and God restores me.

27:48.027 --> 27:55.957
Maybe there's, maybe in my life now, maybe there's, you know, I'm knowing what it is to overcome sin and temptation.

27:56.258 --> 27:59.102
So my sanctification improves, yeah?

27:59.662 --> 28:05.490
But what we need to understand is that my salvation is not based.

28:05.634 --> 28:08.858
on my sanctity, oh he's put my chart up there now, isn't he?

28:09.198 --> 28:10.680
Alright, so, thanks Johnny.

28:11.181 --> 28:16.407
So, there is Lucas' line of salvation along the top.

28:16.427 --> 28:17.268
You see that?

28:17.288 --> 28:20.252
When I was four, there's a cross on the chart, saved.

28:21.413 --> 28:22.274
Why am I saved?

28:22.895 --> 28:26.479
I'm saved because of what Christ has done for me, yeah?

28:26.500 --> 28:30.484
But then my sanctification, it's not very good, is it really?

28:30.985 --> 28:35.090
So, at four I'm improving, at 14 after that I had a bit of a blip,

28:35.490 --> 28:38.435
And then I had some challenges at about 16.

28:38.455 --> 28:41.720
And then since then, I've just sought to improve.

28:42.181 --> 28:45.085
And according to this chart, I'm gonna live to 70, yeah?

28:45.185 --> 28:45.726
See that there?

28:46.908 --> 28:57.565
And you notice at 70, when I hit the edge, I zoom straight up because at that moment, I will meet Jesus, thanks Johnny, and I will become like him.

28:58.186 --> 29:03.314
I want you to understand this evening that you can have an assurance of faith

29:04.354 --> 29:08.659
Even if sometime, there are moments in our lives where we feel we let God down.

29:09.561 --> 29:12.644
I don't believe you become unsafe and saved every two minutes.

29:13.566 --> 29:16.710
The Bible says that you're a son or you're a daughter of the king.

29:17.050 --> 29:19.553
The Bible says you've been adopted into his family.

29:20.955 --> 29:26.142
The assurance of faith that we have, it's no cockiness or confidence in ourselves.

29:26.862 --> 29:32.850
It's because we absolutely recognize the work of the cross and what Christ has done for us.

29:33.378 --> 29:45.254
And our attitude should be, as Paul talks about in Romans 5 or 6, shall we go on sinning that grace may abound?

29:45.935 --> 29:48.158
Paul says, absolutely not.

29:48.939 --> 29:58.232
If we belong to Him and we love Him, our desire will be that our lives steer clear from sin and we live lives that please Him.

29:58.913 --> 30:02.898
We sang earlier in our songs together, Christ be magnified in me

30:03.234 --> 30:07.239
Christ be magnified from the altar of my life.

30:07.519 --> 30:14.747
A saint who has assurance of faith needs to be someone who says, Christ be magnified in me.

30:15.328 --> 30:23.818
Not that I can add my good works to your salvation of my soul, but that I might please you as your son or your daughter.

30:24.519 --> 30:28.163
This is the verse I want to leave you with this evening, the band can come now.

30:28.203 --> 30:28.603
Thank you.

30:29.104 --> 30:31.026
Ephesians chapter 5 verse 10.

30:32.674 --> 30:36.098
It says simply this, find out what pleases the Lord.

30:37.560 --> 30:52.519
If you love Jesus this evening, if you confess to me as your savior, if you're grateful for the certainty of your salvation, then this should be the posture of your heart tonight, that you'll have that heart that says, Lord, what is it that pleases you?

30:53.180 --> 30:55.743
How can I live my life in a way that's honoring to you?

30:57.385 --> 31:01.330
We're gonna finish our service this evening by singing a hymn together,

31:02.018 --> 31:10.329
It's a song that's rich in theology, and it beautifully expresses Christ's wondrous sacrifice and provision for us.

31:11.591 --> 31:14.976
And there are scores of scriptures that sit behind these verses.

31:15.036 --> 31:20.443
It's a hymn written by Charity Lee Smith called Before the Throne of God.

31:22.005 --> 31:24.368
And I just want to read a couple of the lines to you.

31:25.610 --> 31:31.538
We sing this song together at the end of this Romans road series because it reminds us

31:32.194 --> 31:35.718
that there is one who ever intercedes and prays for us.

31:36.499 --> 31:43.107
And the reason why we can be confident in our salvation is because it's a work of what Christ has done in us.

31:43.187 --> 31:43.848
It's a gift.

31:44.308 --> 31:45.289
It's not by works.

31:45.370 --> 31:46.211
It's by grace.

31:46.811 --> 31:48.393
And he continues to hold us.

31:51.837 --> 31:59.346
Verse two says these words, because the sinless Savior died, my sinful soul is counted free.

32:00.034 --> 32:06.220
for God that just is satisfied to look on him and pardon me.

32:08.002 --> 32:15.569
And then in the final verse, the writer writes these words, one with himself, I cannot die.

32:16.310 --> 32:19.413
My soul is purchased by his blood.

32:20.194 --> 32:28.562
My life is hid with Christ on high, with Christ my Savior and my God.

32:29.058 --> 32:37.711
Father, we thank you for the truth of your word this evening that everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved.

32:37.731 --> 32:45.183
We thank you for that assurance of faith that we can have tonight because Lord this evening none of us are relying on our own good works.

32:46.164 --> 32:52.214
But Lord it's you that saved us and it's Lord it's you that continues to keep us saved.

32:53.095 --> 32:57.522
Lord I pray this evening that all of us will have that assurance of faith

32:57.634 --> 33:06.748
And Lord, if there is any one part of this congregation this evening that's never trusted you as Savior, Lord, thank you that they too can have that assurance of faith.

33:07.349 --> 33:15.101
If we confess with our mouth that Jesus is Lord, and we believe in our heart that God grays in from the dead, and we can be saved.

33:15.902 --> 33:21.091
And so Lord, I pray that there will or even this evening be people that put their faith and their trust in you.

33:21.932 --> 33:23.314
And Lord, I pray this evening,

33:23.714 --> 33:38.517
I believe, Lord, that You want us to know this truth, so not that our lives live from a place of apathy, but, Lord, that we live from a place of deep appreciation of the Son of God who loved me and gave Himself for me.

33:39.138 --> 33:44.346
I pray that there will be a healthy response in our hearts towards this truth this evening.

33:44.907 --> 33:52.338
The Lord, as we recognize what You have already done for us, the response of our hearts will simply be to want to please You.

33:52.610 --> 33:54.212
with every part of our lives.

33:54.713 --> 33:58.158
We thank you for the salvation gift that you've given to us.

33:58.839 --> 34:05.209
And I pray that your teachers to use all that you've given us in a way that's honouring to you.

34:08.193 --> 34:08.293
Amen.

34:08.313 --> 34:09.815
We've come to the end of this week's message.

34:10.456 --> 34:12.099
We hope you've been impacted and inspired.

34:12.920 --> 34:19.730
Please keep up to date with everything that's happening by visiting our website at www.livechurchbarrington.com.

